<paragraph id="8B9336C3BE3DFA7EFF553897FB01FE9E" blockId="1.[136,1452,159,327]" pageId="1" pageNumber="95">
<emphasis id="B958EAD1BE3DFA7EFF553897FF27FF6E" bold="true" box="[136,200,159,183]" pageId="1" pageNumber="95">Notes</emphasis>
:— 
<taxonomicName id="4C2C4D40BE3DFA7EFF373897FE1EFF6E" authority="Sw." authorityName="Swartz" authorityYear="1788" box="[234,497,159,183]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Melastoma" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="1" pageNumber="95" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ornatum">
<emphasis id="B958EAD1BE3DFA7EFF373897FE2CFF6E" box="[234,451,159,183]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="95">Melastoma ornatum</emphasis>
Sw.
</taxonomicName>
is the oldest basionym for this species and it was omitted from the list of synonyms by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFBD4B32BE3DFA7EFF5538CBFE61FF02" author="Guimaraes, P. J. F. &amp; Michelangeli F. A. &amp; Sosa, K. &amp; Santiago, J. R." box="[136,398,195,219]" pageId="1" pageNumber="95" pagination="937 - 1002" refId="ref2118" refString="Guimaraes, P. J. F., Michelangeli F. A., Sosa, K. &amp; Santiago, J. R. (2019) Systematics of Tibouchina and allies (Melastomataceae: Melastomateae): a new taxonomic classification. Taxon 68: 937 - 1002. https: // doi. org / 10.1002 / tax. 12151" type="journal article" year="2019">
Guimarães 
<emphasis id="B958EAD1BE3DFA7EFED938CCFED4FF02" box="[260,315,195,219]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="95">et al.</emphasis>
(2019)
</bibRefCitation>
. Because the combination 
<taxonomicName id="4C2C4D40BE3DFA7EFD6C38CBFAC5FF02" authority="(Vahl) P. J. F. Guim. &amp; Michelang." authorityName="P. J. F. Guim. &amp; Michelang." baseAuthorityName="Vahl" box="[689,1322,195,219]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Chaetogastra" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="1" pageNumber="95" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="inconstans">
<emphasis id="B958EAD1BE3DFA7EFD6C38CBFC52FF02" box="[689,957,195,219]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="95">Chaetogastra inconstans</emphasis>
(Vahl) P.J.F.Guim. &amp; Michelang.
</taxonomicName>
is based on a more recent synonym (
<taxonomicName id="4C2C4D40BE3DFA7EFE4B38EFFCE1FF26" authority="Vahl (1797: 37)" authorityName="Vahl" authorityPageNumber="37" authorityYear="1797" box="[406,782,231,255]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Rhexia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="1" pageNumber="95" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="inconstans">
<emphasis id="B958EAD1BE3DFA7EFE4B38EFFDB5FF26" box="[406,602,231,255]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="95">Rhexia inconstans</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFBD4B32BE3DFA7EFDBE38EFFCE1FF26" author="Vahl, M." box="[611,782,231,255]" pageId="1" pageNumber="95" refId="ref2621" refString="Vahl, M. (1797) Eclogae americanae, seu, Descriptiones plantarum praesertim Americae meridionalis, nondum cognitarum. Vol. 1. Havniae [Copenhagen]: Impensis Auctoris, 52 pp. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 429" type="book" year="1797">Vahl (1797: 37)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, a new combination for the basionym with priority is needed. 
<bibRefCitation id="EFBD4B32BE3DFA7EFF553903FE65FEFA" author="Guimaraes, P. J. F. &amp; Michelangeli F. A. &amp; Sosa, K. &amp; Santiago, J. R." box="[136,394,267,291]" pageId="1" pageNumber="95" pagination="937 - 1002" refId="ref2118" refString="Guimaraes, P. J. F., Michelangeli F. A., Sosa, K. &amp; Santiago, J. R. (2019) Systematics of Tibouchina and allies (Melastomataceae: Melastomateae): a new taxonomic classification. Taxon 68: 937 - 1002. https: // doi. org / 10.1002 / tax. 12151" type="journal article" year="2019">
Guimarães 
<emphasis id="B958EAD1BE3DFA7EFED93904FED4FEFA" box="[260,315,267,291]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="95">et al.</emphasis>
(2019)
</bibRefCitation>
designated a 
<typeStatus id="54978861BE3DFA7EFDFC3903FD6CFEFA" box="[545,643,267,291]" pageId="1" pageNumber="95">lectotype</typeStatus>
for 
<taxonomicName id="4C2C4D40BE3DFA7EFD6E3903FC8AFEFA" authorityName="Swartz" authorityYear="1798" baseAuthorityName="Sw." box="[691,869,267,291]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Osbeckia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="1" pageNumber="95" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ornata">
<emphasis id="B958EAD1BE3DFA7EFD6E3903FC8AFEFA" box="[691,869,267,291]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="95">Osbeckia ornata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
unaware of the designation already made by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFBD4B32BE3DFA7EFA883903FF20FE9E" author="Howard, R." pageId="1" pageNumber="95" pagination="399 - 402" refId="ref2182" refString="Howard, R. (1972) Notes of Tibouchina and Charianthus (Melastomataceae) in the Lesser Antilles. Journal of the Arnold Arboretum 53: 399 - 402." type="journal article" year="1972">Howard (1972)</bibRefCitation>
for 
<taxonomicName id="4C2C4D40BE3DFA7EFF213927FE3CFE9E" authorityName="Swartz" authorityYear="1788" box="[252,467,303,327]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Melastoma" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="1" pageNumber="95" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ornatum">
<emphasis id="B958EAD1BE3DFA7EFF213927FE3CFE9E" box="[252,467,303,327]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="95">Melastoma ornatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The first designation of the 
<typeStatus id="54978861BE3DFA7EFCD53927FC85FE9E" box="[776,874,303,327]" pageId="1" pageNumber="95">lectotype</typeStatus>
has priority and that is noted above.
</paragraph>
